  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bipolar Disorder show cyclic changes of mood between depression (depressive phase) and mania
      (maniac phase). Vestibular tests have been shown high sensibility and specificity as a
      biological marker for major depression. This exploratory investigation will measure and
      compare the vestibular activity of bipolar disorder patients during different phases ( 6
      depressed phase, 6 maniac phase, 6 euthimic and 6 control healthy subjects).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
